post_text:
The Mohawk Warrior Football Team will take on Cornell in the first scrimmage of the season tomorrow, September 4, 2020, at 7 pm. At the present time, activities and gatherings held outdoors are limited to no more than 250 people. However, the Governor has relaxed the ban on spectators. Tickets will be distributed to athletes and appropriate personnel. No admittance will be granted without a ticket.

Face coverings must be worn until you are seated. Please sit with family members only and maintain social distancing of 6 feet from others. Stands will be marked to assist with distancing.

As guidance changes, the district will continuously review state and health department mandates for future Mohawk events. We are very happy to welcome spectators to Warrior Stadium!

As always, GO WARRIORS!
#WarriorPRIDE

post_text: Welcome back Mohawk! We are excited to begin the new school year tomorrow, August 31st. Remember that we are now on an hour delay start. Also the high school is running on a hybrid schedule that can be found on our website’s calendar. We are beginning Monday with all high school students with last names that begin with letters A-L. Tuesday will be all high school students with last names beginning with letters M-Z. We wish everyone a fantastic school year and remember to wear your mask!

ELLWOOD is committed to providing ongoing education and training. This increases opportunities for employees to use their talents in ways that contribute to their professional growth and to our continued success. 💪📚

Below is just one example: The Ellwood Quality Steels Steelmaking Class. And, we were fortunate to have with us this week Lori Boston, a math teacher from the Mohawk Area School District, who has sought out industries and is making her curriculum applicable. Thank you, Lori for your commitment to your students and your community!

Kindergarten registration for the 2020/21 school year will take place at the elementary school on July 29th and 30th. The school will be contacting each parent or guardian of a child that has submitted a registration packet. A date and time will be assigned to each student. We will also explain the safety protocols and procedures for the day. We look forward to meeting our new kindergarten students and parents.

If you have not submitted a packet, you may do so on-line or pick one up at the elementary office.

If you have any questions or concerns, please contact Mr. Sperdute.

post_text: We want to know what you have been up to during quarantine! Have you learned a new skill? Choreographed a dance with your family? Created something awesome? Send us a 10 second video showcasing how you've spent your time or how you're making the most of your time at home! We will select the best 10 videos and post them to social media, where we will let you all decide the winners! The top three videos will receive a special prize. Submit entries to moshane@mohawk.k12.pa.us until Monday, April 27. We will then post on Facebook, Instagram, Mohawk Website and Google Classroom for voting with final results announced May 1st. Third place will receive a $25 Visa Gift Card, Second Place will receive a $50 Visa Gift Card and First Place will receive a $100 Visa Gift Card.

Submit entries to moshane@mohawk.k12.pa.us until Monday, April 27. We will then post on Facebook, Instagram, Mohawk Website and Google Classroom for voting with final results announced May 1st. Third place will receive a $25 Visa Gift Card, Second Place will receive a $50 Visa Gift Card and First Place will receive a $100 Visa Gift Card.

If you do not have internet, the elementary parking lot has FREE wifi that you can access from outside the building either in the front or rear parking lot. You must use a district owned chromebook to access the wifi. Students can also do work offline in Google Docs, sheets and slides. They can then come to campus and upload via the Mohawk wifi.

Student chromebooks will automatically connect to the wifi.

You can access wifi from the parking lot in the front or rear of the building. The strongest signal is closest to the building so refrain from parking in the back of either lot.

Please keep social distancing by staying in your vehicle.

Thank you to students and parents for your participation and positive attitude as we continue to navigate this situation together.

The lunch program will continue for Mohawk students who are eligible for free and reduced meals. If you are currently unemployed, without income or your income status has changed, you may be eligible for meals through the National School Lunch Program. Please complete the application located at www.paschoolmeals.com. The application may be completed online or on paper and returned to Mrs. Norma Huff (nhuff@mohawk.k12.pa.us).

The following changes in times and locations will begin on Monday, March 23, 2020. Students may obtain a “grab and go” breakfast and lunch daily, Monday through Friday, at the following locations between 11:30 and noon:

Mohawk High School Gymnasium Entrance
MoCo House Bessemer
Soccer Field Hillsville
Enon Valley Presbyterian Church and Freed’s MHP
Delivery throughout the following Mobile Home Parks: Twilight and Zoccoli

post_text: Today, Governor Tom Wolf announced that all K-12 Pennsylvania schools will be closed for ten business days effective Monday, March 16, 2020. The Mohawk Area School District is closed beginning Monday, March 16 through Friday, March 27. Further updates will be provided in the coming days about instructional pathways for learning continuity. We will continue to monitor state and public health guidance and use student health and safety as our priority in decision making. Thank you for your cooperation as we deal with this situation as a Mohawk School Community.

post_text: The Business Management class welcomed Ed & Dylan Stevens of Stevens Masonry Construction, Inc. Dylan shared key points that will help make the students successful not only in business, but also as individuals. Ed & Dylan shared information on their business history, getting started, and the need for having a good accountant, business attorney and insurance agent.

On Tuesday, May 12th and Wednesday, May 13th Mohawk Elementary is holding kindergarten screening for children who will be five years of age on/before September 1, 2020.

Please contact the school to pick up the enrollment packet that has to be filled out completely and returned in order to schedule your child's screening.

If you have any questions, feel free to call Mrs. Wrona at 724-667-7782 ext 1100 between the hours of 8:30am and 3:00pm.
